.SH CONFIGURATION
.LP
A default configuration file is automatically generated at: \f(CR\(ti/.config/carnage/carnage.toml\fR
.PP
It is automatically reset to default when a key is missing or is unparseable.
.PP
Additionally, a empty command override configuration file is automatically generated at: \f(CR\(ti/.config/carnage/commands.toml\fR
.PP
It allows advanced users to override the exact commands executed for various operations, including adding custom flags, changing environment variables, or even replacing the underlying tools entirely.
.PP
Variables \f(CR$1\fR, \f(CR$2\fR, etc. are replaced with arguments passed by carnage. The \f(CRprivilege\fR field controls whether the command needs escalation (uses \f(CRprivilege_backend\fR when \f(CRtrue\fR). The \f(CRenvironment\fR field sets additional environment variables for that command only.
.PP
This file is intended for advanced users only; incorrect configurations may cause operations to fail in unexpected ways.
.PP
The main configuration file uses the \c
.UR https://toml.io/
TOML
.UE
